        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(qa): crabline channel driver",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nThis PR makes QA profile channel drivers executable and separates channel identity from transport mode.\n\n- Runs the `smoke-ci` QA profile through Crabline local mocks, defaulting to the Telegram channel shape without requiring Telegram credentials or Convex leases.\n- Adds a Crabline-backed QA transport that maps requested channel IDs such as `telegram` or `slack` onto local mock providers and records native QA evidence through the QA Lab bus.\n- Keeps live channel execution on the native live transports, where unsupported requested channels fail as missing coverage instead of silently falling back.\n- Makes the `release` live profile fan out to the native Matrix, Telegram, Discord, Slack, and WhatsApp live lane catalogs, then merges their `qa-evidence.json` outputs into one profile evidence artifact.\n- Converts Matrix live QA to emit native QA evidence while preserving its Matrix-specific diagnostic summary.\n\n## Why\n\n`smoke-ci` should be a deterministic CI profile for channel-shaped behavior, not a secret-bearing live service run. Live service coverage belongs in the live transport lanes and release profile evidence. Keeping those concepts separate lets tests ask for `channel: telegram` while the selected profile decides whether that Telegram-shaped exchange is mocked locally or executed against the real Telegram transport.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check .github/workflows/qa-live-transports-convex.yml extensions/qa-lab/src/crabline-channel-driver.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/crabline-channel-driver.test.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/crabline-transport.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/crabline-transport.test.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/suite.test.ts`\n- `pnpm exec tsgo --noEmit -p tsconfig.extensions.json`\n- `pnpm vitest run extensions/qa-lab/src/crabline-transport.test.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/crabline-channel-driver.test.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/suite.test.ts test/scripts/package-acceptance-workflow.test.ts`\n",
